a very simple java code to test (given that you have imported web3j as a dependency, see http://docs.web3j.io/getting_started/#gradle) is:
```
import java.net.ConnectException;
import org.web3j.protocol.Web3j;
import org.web3j.protocol.websocket.WebSocketService;

public class Main {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    final WebSocketService wss = new WebSocketService("ws://localhost:7546", true);
    try {
      wss.connect();
    } catch (final ConnectException e) {
      System.out.println("ConnectException: " + e.getMessage());
    }
    Web3j.build(wss);
  }
}
```

