Concerning Issue#490, After looking at these docs, I believe you shouldn't get the miner's Id, but rather submit a random ID string. 

https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/blob/master/EIPS/eip-1474.md#eth_submithashrate
https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/JSON-RPC#eth_submithashrate 


https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/a91b704b013aaabb3bfc796f5a3d8c940dfb7f05/consensus/ethash/api.go#L86
```
// SubmitHashrate can be used for remote miners to submit their hash rate.
// This enables the node to report the combined hash rate of all miners
// which submit work through this node.
//
// It accepts the miner hash rate and an identifier which must be unique
// between nodes.
```

